<div class="mdui-typo"><h1 id="neat-adj">neat <strong><em>adj</em></strong></h1>
<p>英 /niːt/    美 /niːt/  </p>
<h2 id="_1">释义</h2>
<h4 id="1">1.★ <strong>(场所) 整洁的；整齐的：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>He always keeps his desk neat.
他总是保持桌子整洁。</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>I arranged all the books in a neat row.
我把所有的书整整齐齐地排好。</p><footer>人教新必修③ – 3改</footer></div>

<h4 id="2">2.★ <strong>(人) (爱) 整洁的：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>a very neat woman 
装束十分整洁的女人</p></div>

<h4 id="3-ame">3.<strong>[非正式用语] (AmE) 好的；极好的；令人愉快的：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>We had a great time yesterday— it was pretty neat.
我们昨天玩得很愉快，棒极了。</p></div>

<h2 id="_2">派生词汇</h2>
<p>neatly /niːtli/ adv   </p></div>